cs.SE, cs.PL, cs.CR, cs.SI, cs.LG. 

This paper focuses on the usage, updates, and risks of third-party libraries in software development, which is a common concern in software engineering (cs.SE). The study specifically analyzes Java projects, which falls under programming languages (cs.PL). The risk analysis of outdated libraries also relates to computer security (cs.CR) and system integrity (cs.SI). Finally, the proposed bug-driven alerting system involves machine learning (cs.LG) to assist developers in making decisions.
